06/11/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Federation of Unions in Education "Spiru Haret" has filed a complaint with the European Parliament (EP) over the government's decision to postpone by six months a 50% raise for teachers, media reported on Wednesday (November 5th). 
The complaint went to the EP's Petition Committee. 
The EP is expected to ask for the Romanian parliament's opinion on the case before it makes a decision. 
The government insists the raise is unaffordable.
In other news Wednesday, Transport Minister Ludovic Orban threatened to sue railway workers over a strike they plan for Friday. 
They are protesting management decisions regarding the state railway, Caile Ferate Romane. 
(Ziare, Mediafax, Realitatea TV - 05/11/08)
